<% content_for :title, "Add a Feed" %>

<h2 class="mb-4">Add a Feed</h2>

<p class="mb-4">
  Enter the URL of the RSS or Atom feed you want to monitor.
</p>

<div class="mb-4">
  <label for="feed_url" class="form-label">Feed URL</label>
  <input type="url" class="form-control" id="feed_url" name="feed_url" placeholder="https://example.com/feed.xml">
  <div class="form-text">
    Enter the full URL of an RSS or Atom feed.
  </div>
</div>

<div id="feed-detection-status" class="d-none">
  <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-start mb-3">
        <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Feed Detected</h6>
        <span class="badge bg-success">Valid Feed</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-3">
        <label for="feed_profile" class="form-label">Feed Type</label>
        <select class="form-select" id="feed_profile" name="feed_profile">
          <option value="rss" selected>RSS/Atom Feed</option>
          <option value="xkcd">XKCD Comic</option>
          <option value="other">Other</option>
        </select>
        <div class="form-text">
          The detected feed type. Change if needed.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-3">
        <label for="feed_name" class="form-label">Feed Name</label>
        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="feed_name" name="feed_name" value="Example Feed" maxlength="40">
        <div class="form-text">
          A friendly name for this feed. You can change it if you like.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-3">
        <label for="feed_description" class="form-label">Description (optional)</label>
        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="feed_description" name="feed_description" placeholder="Add a description" maxlength="100">
      </div>

      <div class="d-flex gap-2">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary" id="preview-feed">
          Preview in Browser
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
  <strong>Not sure where to find a feed URL?</strong>
  <p class="mb-0 mt-2">
    Most blogs and news sites have RSS feeds. Look for an RSS icon or link labeled "Feed", "RSS", or "Atom". You can also try adding "/feed" or "/rss" to the end of a website URL.
  </p>
</div>
